\doTocEntry\toclof{}{\csname a:TocLink\endcsname{16}{x16-223002}{}{\numberline {8.1}{\ignorespaces The three bases of this subsection, seen geometrically. Each basis fixes the nonbasic variables at zero, which places the basic solution at the intersection of two constraint boundaries. Bases $\{x_1,x_2\}$ and $\{s_1,s_2\}$ give basic \emph {feasible} solutions at the vertices $(6,5)$ and $(0,0)$ (filled dots). Basis $\{x_1,s_2\}$ gives the basic solution $(16,0)$ (open dot), the intersection of the $x_1$-axis ($x_2=0$) with the boundary $x_1+2x_2=16$ ($s_1=0$); it violates $5x_1+3x_2\le 45$, so it is an infeasible basic solution and lies outside the region.\relax }}}{496}\relax 
